      2. ...
      (Exercise 1 The ideal of value-free science)
         • Science: value-free? yes/no? 
         • Intrinsic values of science
            ▸ honesty
            ▸ fairness
            ▸ objectivity
            ▸ increase of knowledge (or wellfare)
            ▸ rationality
         • interacting values
            ▸ value system of researcher
            ▸ value system of society (via funding)
           interaction by determining what is being studied and providing resources, but also results interact with values (both ways)

         • Code of Conducts

